00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:32,000
=Our Days=

2
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,720
(Adapted from Lang Lang's original novel
"The Prime of the Goddess")

3
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:38,160
=Episode 28=

4
00:01:38,550 --> 00:01:39,520
Gao Ping.

5
00:01:40,389 --> 00:01:41,279
Miss,

6
00:01:41,509 --> 00:01:42,549
have you seen

7
00:01:42,550 --> 00:01:43,759
anyone in this room?

8
00:01:44,669 --> 00:01:46,880
I haven't cleaned that room yet.

9
00:01:47,469 --> 00:01:48,069
I don't think

10
00:01:48,070 --> 00:01:49,719
the guest came outside.

11
00:01:50,550 --> 00:01:51,359
Thank you.

12
00:01:52,550 --> 00:01:53,680
Gao Ping,

13
00:01:54,150 --> 00:01:55,228
I just want to talk to you.

14
00:01:55,229 --> 00:01:56,600
Can you open the door?

15
00:02:50,390 --> 00:02:51,279
Gao Ping.

16
00:02:54,589 --> 00:02:55,480
Gao Ping.

17
00:02:57,430 --> 00:03:00,200
Gao Ping, watch out.

18
00:03:02,869 --> 00:03:03,839
What are you doing?

19
00:03:08,029 --> 00:03:08,829
Deng Haiyang, what's up?

20
00:03:08,830 --> 00:03:09,960
I have something going on.

21
00:03:10,550 --> 00:03:11,680
I saw Gao Ping.

22
00:03:13,189 --> 00:03:14,200
Alright, I got it.

23
00:03:14,469 --> 00:03:14,908
What's wrong?

24
00:03:14,909 --> 00:03:15,509
Deng Haiyang is here.

25
00:03:15,510 --> 00:03:16,960
He said Gao Ping was over there.

26
00:03:17,789 --> 00:03:19,039
That way.

27
00:03:31,189 --> 00:03:32,240
Deng Haiyang.

28
00:03:32,909 --> 00:03:33,989
Aren't you...

29
00:03:33,990 --> 00:03:35,468
Aren't you looking for him?

30
00:03:35,469 --> 00:03:36,240
I...

31
00:03:37,029 --> 00:03:38,200
What is he doing?

32
00:03:42,710 --> 00:03:44,080
Should we call the police?

33
00:03:50,950 --> 00:03:52,080
Gao Ping.

34
00:04:02,789 --> 00:04:03,559
Sir,

35
00:04:03,710 --> 00:04:05,760
can you please help pick him up?

36
00:04:12,270 --> 00:04:13,319
Are you alright?

37
00:04:19,830 --> 00:04:21,240
Come on, come on to the boat.

38
00:04:21,789 --> 00:04:22,839
Hurry up.

39
00:04:49,909 --> 00:04:51,269
You've been avoiding me,

40
00:04:51,270 --> 00:04:52,668
are you planning not to see me again

41
00:04:52,669 --> 00:04:53,640
in the future?

42
00:04:55,710 --> 00:04:56,908
Aren't you going to be there

43
00:04:56,909 --> 00:04:57,839
when we get the divorce certificate?

44
00:04:58,310 --> 00:04:59,960
Aren't you still going to see me?

45
00:05:00,870 --> 00:05:02,479
Have we reached the point

46
00:05:03,510 --> 00:05:05,069
where we can't even

47
00:05:05,070 --> 00:05:07,200
sit and talk face-to-face?

48
00:05:09,469 --> 00:05:11,200
If you want to study abroad,

49
00:05:11,589 --> 00:05:12,839
if you want a divorce,

50
00:05:13,669 --> 00:05:15,069
if you want to get rid of this family,

51
00:05:15,070 --> 00:05:16,389
if you want to get rid of
me and the kids,

52
00:05:16,390 --> 00:05:17,960
you can tell me directly.

53
00:05:19,870 --> 00:05:20,799
Gao Ping,

54
00:05:22,029 --> 00:05:23,640
from the time we met
and got married until now,

55
00:05:24,109 --> 00:05:26,359
for these five years,

56
00:05:28,109 --> 00:05:30,320
I've supported you
no matter what you wanted to do.

57
00:05:33,469 --> 00:05:35,000
I have been working so hard out there

58
00:05:35,029 --> 00:05:38,120
and making money to support the family,

59
00:05:39,310 --> 00:05:42,069
but I have never allowed you

60
00:05:42,070 --> 00:05:42,949
to face any pressure in life

61
00:05:42,950 --> 00:05:44,479
when you were studying,

62
00:05:45,150 --> 00:05:46,039
right?

63
00:05:47,950 --> 00:05:48,919
Of course,

64
00:05:49,390 --> 00:05:50,588
you have taken excellent care

65
00:05:50,589 --> 00:05:51,960
of Cong and Qi,

66
00:05:52,190 --> 00:05:53,839
you provided them with a lot of love.

67
00:05:55,429 --> 00:05:57,389
I feel that in our relationship,

68
00:05:57,390 --> 00:05:59,520
there aren't any major conflicts.

69
00:06:01,190 --> 00:06:02,228
So I can't figure out

70
00:06:02,229 --> 00:06:05,039
why we should separate this way.

71
00:06:08,349 --> 00:06:09,279
I didn't want this either.

72
00:06:09,310 --> 00:06:11,479
But you have already done it.

73
00:06:12,669 --> 00:06:14,719
You brought Li Shu to our home,

74
00:06:15,029 --> 00:06:16,640
made me doubt you,

75
00:06:17,429 --> 00:06:18,919
we fought,

76
00:06:20,349 --> 00:06:21,799
you left the house,

77
00:06:24,349 --> 00:06:26,309
you even accused me of being paranoid

78
00:06:26,310 --> 00:06:27,640
and didn't trust you.

79
00:06:28,989 --> 00:06:30,599
Why do we have to end up like this?

80
00:06:33,190 --> 00:06:34,440
If I

81
00:06:35,510 --> 00:06:38,080
have another honest path to take,

82
00:06:40,750 --> 00:06:42,320
I wouldn't want to
cause all these either.

83
00:06:44,510 --> 00:06:46,159
I have joined the postdoctoral program.

84
00:06:46,789 --> 00:06:48,359
But no matter
how skilled I am in my field

85
00:06:49,909 --> 00:06:51,359
or how many papers I publish,

86
00:06:52,429 --> 00:06:54,599
no school would take me in two years.

87
00:06:55,950 --> 00:06:57,520
Because my initial academic background
is too weak.

88
00:07:00,669 --> 00:07:02,200
I have been studying all my life.

89
00:07:04,950 --> 00:07:06,599
I don't know how to do anything else.

90
00:07:10,589 --> 00:07:11,960
What am I going to do?

91
00:07:13,789 --> 00:07:15,228
Every single day I've stayed here,

92
00:07:15,229 --> 00:07:17,668
I just feel like a loach.

93
00:07:17,669 --> 00:07:20,080
I'm lying in a stinky ditch.

94
00:07:21,549 --> 00:07:24,320
No matter how much I struggle or flail,

95
00:07:25,669 --> 00:07:28,239
I just can't get out
of that stinky ditch.

96
00:07:30,989 --> 00:07:32,269
There are clearly good schools

97
00:07:32,270 --> 00:07:34,468
and good institutes overseas.

98
00:07:34,469 --> 00:07:35,668
I can go out there and give it a try.

99
00:07:35,669 --> 00:07:36,788
I can just try.

100
00:07:36,789 --> 00:07:40,359
Why do I have to lie in this smelly ditch?

101
00:07:44,109 --> 00:07:45,880
But how can I get out?

102
00:07:48,710 --> 00:07:49,919
I am committed to you.

103
00:07:51,150 --> 00:07:52,839
I am committed to Cong and Qi.

104
00:07:54,029 --> 00:07:55,629
What right do I have

105
00:07:55,630 --> 00:07:57,640
to ask you to accompany me abroad?

106
00:07:58,789 --> 00:08:01,279
Sometimes I try to persuade myself
to just forget it,

107
00:08:02,029 --> 00:08:03,960
but I really don't know

108
00:08:04,390 --> 00:08:07,440
how can I make myself give up willingly.

109
00:08:14,750 --> 00:08:15,869
Do you remember
the exchange student opportunity

110
00:08:15,870 --> 00:08:17,679
in the U.S. three years ago?

111
00:08:18,909 --> 00:08:22,359
At that time, you said
because of your parents, your sisters,

112
00:08:22,589 --> 00:08:24,719
Cong and Qi's studies,

113
00:08:26,190 --> 00:08:27,149
you couldn't go.

114
00:08:27,150 --> 00:08:27,788
Yes,

115
00:08:27,789 --> 00:08:29,159
I certainly know that.

116
00:08:30,270 --> 00:08:31,320
You said, husband and wife

117
00:08:31,349 --> 00:08:32,960
can't be separated for so long.

118
00:08:34,549 --> 00:08:37,279
I knew that I would be sacrificing
in the end.

119
00:08:38,390 --> 00:08:39,720
But the problem is

120
00:08:40,429 --> 00:08:42,319
how long will I have to sacrifice?

121
00:08:43,549 --> 00:08:44,319
I...

122
00:08:44,429 --> 00:08:47,229
Am I supposed
to keep living like a parasite

123
00:08:47,230 --> 00:08:48,799
for the rest of my life?

124
00:09:01,510 --> 00:09:03,159
I really don't know

125
00:09:04,669 --> 00:09:06,679
what else I can do but divorce.

126
00:09:08,069 --> 00:09:10,120
You could've at least been direct.

127
00:09:12,630 --> 00:09:14,400
The reason why
you didn't want to tell me

128
00:09:14,789 --> 00:09:15,589
is because you didn't want to

129
00:09:15,590 --> 00:09:17,039
be the bad guy.

130
00:09:19,270 --> 00:09:21,068
You want to divorce gracefully

131
00:09:21,069 --> 00:09:22,360
and protect yourself.

132
00:09:24,709 --> 00:09:26,079
But have you ever thought about this?

133
00:09:27,230 --> 00:09:29,120
All your behaviors

134
00:09:29,309 --> 00:09:31,039
will have an effect on Cong and Qi.

135
00:09:33,669 --> 00:09:34,640
It's true that...

136
00:09:40,630 --> 00:09:42,279
they are not your biological children.

137
00:09:46,470 --> 00:09:48,480
But they have called you Dad

138
00:09:51,429 --> 00:09:53,039
ever since they learned how to speak.

139
00:09:58,390 --> 00:09:59,589
What am I supposed to tell

140
00:09:59,590 --> 00:10:01,428
the two kids that the man
whom they've called 'Dad' for five years

141
00:10:01,429 --> 00:10:02,760
doesn't want them anymore?

142
00:10:06,350 --> 00:10:08,679
Will your conscience not be condemned?

143
00:10:20,110 --> 00:10:21,079
I'm sorry.

144
00:10:21,909 --> 00:10:23,120
It's too late.

145
00:10:25,829 --> 00:10:27,520
I don't want to forgive you now.

146
00:11:12,949 --> 00:11:13,720
Let's go.

147
00:11:34,549 --> 00:11:35,640
Here.

148
00:11:49,709 --> 00:11:50,869
I trust your vision.

149
00:11:50,870 --> 00:11:51,749
You can never go wrong.

150
00:11:51,750 --> 00:11:53,640
I don't trust anyone but you.

151
00:11:53,789 --> 00:11:54,679
Biao.

152
00:11:55,029 --> 00:11:56,120
Apologies, everyone,

153
00:11:56,350 --> 00:11:57,319
we are late.

154
00:11:57,630 --> 00:11:58,600
Let me introduce,

155
00:11:58,630 --> 00:12:00,039
this is Xiang Nan,

156
00:12:00,110 --> 00:12:00,919
my wife.

157
00:12:01,470 --> 00:12:02,559
This is Biao.

158
00:12:03,270 --> 00:12:04,109
Hi, Mr. Biao.

159
00:12:04,110 --> 00:12:04,908
Hongbin,

160
00:12:04,909 --> 00:12:06,229
we have been waiting for you two.

161
00:12:06,230 --> 00:12:07,480
What took you so long?

162
00:12:08,949 --> 00:12:09,919
Come, have a seat.

163
00:12:10,709 --> 00:12:11,439
Serve the tea.

164
00:12:11,590 --> 00:12:12,319
Xiang Nan.

165
00:12:17,029 --> 00:12:18,319
Mr. Biao, I'm sorry

166
00:12:19,069 --> 00:12:21,720
that I made an extra leg

167
00:12:22,270 --> 00:12:23,959
for the toad I gifted you.

168
00:12:25,590 --> 00:12:27,149
I didn't know

169
00:12:27,150 --> 00:12:28,908
the reference of the three-legged toad,

170
00:12:28,909 --> 00:12:30,109
and it was an unintentional mistake.

171
00:12:30,110 --> 00:12:31,229
I am sorry

172
00:12:31,230 --> 00:12:32,679
for embarrassing you.

173
00:12:32,990 --> 00:12:33,880
My wife

174
00:12:34,029 --> 00:12:35,640
shouldn't be blamed entirely
for this matter.

175
00:12:36,150 --> 00:12:37,520
It's my fault
that I didn't make it clear.

176
00:12:37,789 --> 00:12:38,908
You should think about

177
00:12:38,909 --> 00:12:40,720
how to make up for your mistake then.

178
00:12:40,990 --> 00:12:42,799
What I make isn't worth much.

179
00:12:43,069 --> 00:12:44,319
They are just glass.

180
00:12:44,949 --> 00:12:46,360
Don't say that.

181
00:12:46,870 --> 00:12:49,360
You could become a great artist

182
00:12:49,429 --> 00:12:51,520
and your works will be worth a lot then.

183
00:12:52,270 --> 00:12:53,159
Jiang Hongbin,

184
00:12:53,309 --> 00:12:54,389
you should properly present

185
00:12:54,390 --> 00:12:55,480
your wife.

186
00:12:55,549 --> 00:12:56,428
She might earn

187
00:12:56,429 --> 00:12:57,959
even more than you in the future.

188
00:12:59,510 --> 00:13:01,159
Alright, this is over.

189
00:13:02,630 --> 00:13:03,149
Have a seat.

190
00:13:03,150 --> 00:13:04,039
Come, sit.

191
00:13:04,590 --> 00:13:05,520
This way.

192
00:13:06,750 --> 00:13:07,679
Okay, thank you.

193
00:13:30,630 --> 00:13:31,880
You must be Mrs. Jiang.

194
00:13:32,750 --> 00:13:34,360
Hi, you are...

195
00:13:35,390 --> 00:13:37,428
My husband Fang has a steel business.

196
00:13:37,429 --> 00:13:38,629
We have been

197
00:13:38,630 --> 00:13:40,159
cooperating with Jiang for years.

198
00:13:41,069 --> 00:13:42,199
Sorry,

199
00:13:42,309 --> 00:13:43,548
I am not really familiar

200
00:13:43,549 --> 00:13:44,308
with his friends

201
00:13:44,309 --> 00:13:45,469
from his business circle.

202
00:13:45,470 --> 00:13:46,279
Right,

203
00:13:46,510 --> 00:13:47,989
we have never seen you

204
00:13:47,990 --> 00:13:49,679
in our gatherings.

205
00:13:53,150 --> 00:13:53,959
Here.

206
00:13:56,470 --> 00:13:57,720
This is...

207
00:14:05,270 --> 00:14:06,679
I didn't even notice.

208
00:14:08,029 --> 00:14:09,079
Thank you.

209
00:14:09,549 --> 00:14:10,720
You are welcome.

210
00:14:25,669 --> 00:14:26,760
Thanks to you.

211
00:14:26,909 --> 00:14:27,760
It's nothing.

212
00:14:30,510 --> 00:14:31,400
How about it?

213
00:14:31,470 --> 00:14:32,279
Have you been busy?

214
00:14:36,949 --> 00:14:37,760
Xiang Nan.

215
00:14:38,069 --> 00:14:38,840
Here.

216
00:14:41,829 --> 00:14:42,959
Let me introduce.

217
00:14:43,189 --> 00:14:44,319
This is Mr. Fang

218
00:14:44,549 --> 00:14:45,760
and this is Mrs. Fang.

219
00:14:46,150 --> 00:14:47,149
We have already met

220
00:14:47,150 --> 00:14:48,240
in the hallway.

221
00:14:49,110 --> 00:14:49,919
Right.

222
00:14:50,189 --> 00:14:51,229
Mrs. Fang

223
00:14:51,230 --> 00:14:52,869
did me a huge favour.

224
00:14:52,870 --> 00:14:53,629
Mrs. Jiang,

225
00:14:53,630 --> 00:14:54,629
you are being too kind.

226
00:14:54,630 --> 00:14:55,269
How can Xi

227
00:14:55,270 --> 00:14:56,109
help you in any way?

228
00:14:56,110 --> 00:14:57,149
She doesn't know anything.

229
00:14:57,150 --> 00:14:57,880
Fang,

230
00:14:57,909 --> 00:14:59,599
stop belittling Xi.

231
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:01,188
She is a great artist

232
00:15:01,189 --> 00:15:03,039
graduated from
a professional music school.

233
00:15:03,069 --> 00:15:03,948
She's too good for

234
00:15:03,949 --> 00:15:04,828
you who's unsophisticated.

235
00:15:04,829 --> 00:15:05,389
Right.

236
00:15:05,390 --> 00:15:06,120
Here,

237
00:15:06,590 --> 00:15:07,520
go perform a piece

238
00:15:07,549 --> 00:15:09,000
to liven up the crowd.

239
00:15:09,150 --> 00:15:10,400
That's great!

240
00:15:10,510 --> 00:15:12,319
We are indeed blessed.

241
00:15:13,150 --> 00:15:14,279
If I don't play well,

242
00:15:14,549 --> 00:15:15,880
I hope everyone can understand.

243
00:15:45,429 --> 00:15:46,028
It's agreed then.

244
00:15:46,029 --> 00:15:46,919
Make yourselves at home.

245
00:15:48,270 --> 00:15:49,469
Fang, keep your voice down.

246
00:15:49,470 --> 00:15:50,349
You are scaring me.

247
00:15:50,350 --> 00:15:51,360
Yes.

248
00:16:11,029 --> 00:16:12,079
Here.

249
00:16:16,029 --> 00:16:17,079
Here.

250
00:17:01,829 --> 00:17:04,720
I quite like it here.

251
00:17:05,990 --> 00:17:07,480
Let's meet here for tea next time.

252
00:17:07,630 --> 00:17:08,679
Yes.

253
00:17:09,229 --> 00:17:10,959
She's ignorant because she's young.

254
00:17:11,390 --> 00:17:12,600
Mrs. Jiang,

255
00:17:13,590 --> 00:17:15,080
please let me know about
any good exhibitions in the future

256
00:17:15,310 --> 00:17:16,640
so I can check them out

257
00:17:16,790 --> 00:17:18,120
and gain exposure.

258
00:17:18,669 --> 00:17:19,640
Sure.

259
00:17:20,390 --> 00:17:21,439
Mrs. Fang,

260
00:17:23,390 --> 00:17:25,239
I actually wanted to ask you.

261
00:17:26,229 --> 00:17:28,519
Won't you feel

262
00:17:28,790 --> 00:17:30,040
a little uncomfortable

263
00:17:30,790 --> 00:17:32,320
to perform on such occasions?

264
00:17:34,150 --> 00:17:35,400
I have also asked this question

265
00:17:35,429 --> 00:17:36,880
to myself

266
00:17:37,390 --> 00:17:39,199
when I was around your age.

267
00:17:39,310 --> 00:17:40,880
I stopped thinking about it
anymore after that.

268
00:17:41,150 --> 00:17:42,389
Anyway, whether I'm playing on stage

269
00:17:42,390 --> 00:17:43,759
or below, I'm still playing.

270
00:17:43,949 --> 00:17:45,640
With four strings, it doesn't matter
where I play.

271
00:17:45,830 --> 00:17:48,400
It's all the same.

272
00:17:50,030 --> 00:17:50,988
Xi,

273
00:17:50,989 --> 00:17:52,029
what are you doing?

274
00:17:52,030 --> 00:17:52,959
Let's go.

275
00:17:53,390 --> 00:17:54,360
I should go.

276
00:17:59,989 --> 00:18:01,280
Take care, Mrs. Fang.

277
00:18:12,949 --> 00:18:14,679
I wonder how Mrs. Fang

278
00:18:14,830 --> 00:18:17,519
can be so gracious and decent.

279
00:18:18,669 --> 00:18:19,468
Do you want me to be

280
00:18:19,469 --> 00:18:20,759
someone like that?

281
00:18:22,550 --> 00:18:24,400
You can always learn from others.

282
00:18:25,269 --> 00:18:26,800
Living in a clear and transparent way

283
00:18:27,150 --> 00:18:28,479
can't be a bad thing, right?

284
00:18:31,269 --> 00:18:32,640
Jiang, let me ask you,

285
00:18:33,669 --> 00:18:36,320
do you want me to become a

286
00:18:37,070 --> 00:18:38,040
docile,

287
00:18:38,189 --> 00:18:39,600
